ry will have a useful guide before they begin, while general readers will be able to discover the ways in which the library’s holdings relate to the existing body of literature on the Johnson administration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aBerman, Larry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCulbert, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDivine, Robert A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDivine, Robert A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGelfand, Mark I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraham, Hugh Davis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerring, George C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaFeber, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawson, Steven F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/72031240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292768642423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292768642/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK